<section class="text-content p-3 m-3">
  <div class="container-md p-3 m-3">
    <p class="lead">In JSX, we primarily use the map() function to loop. The map() function lets you manipulate the items in an array by iterating and accessing individual items. You can add <em>index</em> as an optional argument if you need know how many times your loop has iterated. This <em>index</em> can be used to add a corresponding key value to each looped item. React uses these keys to track if items were changed, added, or removed.</p>
  </div>
</section>

